  "text": "CharField max_length validation in Django occurs at four distinct layers:\n\n1. **Field-Level Validation (django/db/models/fields/__init__.py)**:\n   - The CharField class initializes with max_length parameter (line 189, 215)\n   - The __init__ method adds a MaxLengthValidator to the field's validators (line 1209)\n   - The _check_max_length_attribute method performs system checks to ensure max_length is a positive integer (lines 1226-1254)\n   - The deconstruct method includes max_length in field serialization for migrations (line 1312-1315)\n   - The parent Field class includes max_length in its deconstruct method (line 607) so migrations can detect changes\n\n2. **Core Validator (django/core/validators.py)**:\n   - MaxLengthValidator class (line 489) validates that string length does not exceed max_length\n   - This validator is used both in model fields and form fields\n\n3. **Form Field Validation (django/forms/fields.py)**:\n   - CharField in forms also uses MaxLengthValidator (lines 286-287)\n   - The widget_attrs method adds the maxlength HTML attribute to the form widget (lines 302-304)\n   - FileField also implements max_length validation for file names (lines 668-671)\n\n4. **Database Backend Enforcement (multiple backend files)**:\n   - MySQL: Uses VARCHAR(%(max_length)s) SQL type (django/db/backends/mysql/base.py line 116) and validates unique CharField max_length constraints (django/db/backends/mysql/validation.py lines 46-62)\n   - PostgreSQL: Uses varchar(%(max_length)s) SQL type (django/db/backends/postgresql/base.py lines 87-89)\n   - Oracle: Uses NVARCHAR2(%(max_length)s) SQL type (django/db/backends/oracle/base.py line 131)\n   - SQLite: Uses varchar(%(max_length)s) SQL type (django/db/backends/sqlite3/base.py lines 44-46)\n   - Base operations define cast_char_field_without_max_length for fields without max_length\n   - BaseDatabaseValidation provides the framework for backend-specific validation\n\n5. **Migration Auto-Detection (django/db/migrations/autodetector.py and operations/fields.py)**:\n   - MigrationAutodetector.deep_deconstruct (line 74) recursively deconstructs fields including their max_length parameter\n   - MigrationAutodetector.generate_altered_fields (line 1252) detects when field deconstructed representations differ, which includes max_length changes\n   - When max_length changes are detected, AlterField operations are generated\n   - AlterField operation (django/db/migrations/operations/fields.py line 204) encapsulates the max_length change and applies it via schema_editor.alter_field()\n\nThe complete chain flows from model field definition through validators, form representation, database schema generation, and finally migration detection and application."
}

